Context:
The George Brown College offers various programs across different subject areas and interests. These programs include apprenticeships, diplomas, degrees, continuing education, and more. Students can search for programs using the program finder tool, which allows searching by subject matter, job title, credential, and other criteria. Program codes are made up of a letter and three numbers that refer to the full name of the program. For example, H100 is a diploma program in the Centre for Hospitality and Culinary Arts. Students can check the status of programs on Ontario Colleges' Online Application System or the Program Availability page to determine if they can apply. Program codes consist of a letter representing the academic centre and a number representing the credential obtained upon graduation. The college offers a land acknowledgment and provides contact information for inquiries, including phone numbers and email addresses. The information on the website is subject to change without notice.

FACTUAL INFORMATION:
- The college offers apprenticeships, diplomas, degrees, continuing education, and more.
- Students can search for programs using the program finder tool.
- Program codes consist of a letter and three numbers.
- H100 is an example of a diploma program in the Centre for Hospitality and Culinary Arts.
- Students can check the status of programs on Ontario Colleges' Online Application System or the Program Availability page.
- Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca, Social Media Hub link (mentioned twice).
- The college offers a land acknowledgment.
